Detailed Description

PRCM Statistics - API to gather PRCM Statistics.

APIs to program and read the INA226 power measurement ICs

INA226 ADC average configuration values.

Enumerator

Every sample is used. No averaging

Minimum number of averages

PMHAL_INA226_NUM_AVERAGE_4 

4 samples are averaged

PMHAL_INA226_NUM_AVERAGE_16 

16 samples are averaged

64 samples are averaged

256 samples are averaged

512 samples are averaged

1024 samples are averaged

Function Documentation

pmErrCode_t PMHALINA226GetData ( pmhalPrcmPmicRegulatorId_t  voltDomId,
pmhalIna226OutputData_t *  data 
)

Read the INA226 registers to find the voltage and power drawn for a given voltage domain.

Parameters
voltDomIdVoltage Domain ID for which the data needs to be found. Refer pmhalPrcmPmicRegulatorId_t enum for valid values.
dataContainer for the output data. Refer pmhalIna226OutputData_t for details about each output field.
Returns
status PM_SUCCESS When the output data is read correctly. PM_BADARGS When the voltage ID is not valid. PM_FAIL When the output data is not read correctly.
pmErrCode_t PMHALINA226SetAverage ( pmhalPrcmPmicRegulatorId_t  voltDomId,
pmhalIna226NumAverages_t  average 
)

Program the INA226 ADC average number of samples.

Parameters
voltDomIdVoltage Domain ID for which the value needs to be set. Refer pmhalPrcmPmicRegulatorId_t enum for valid values.
averageAverage number of samples for the given INA on the provided voltage rail. Refer pmhalIna226NumAverages_t for valid values.
Returns
status PM_SUCCESS When the average is programmed. PM_BADARGS When the voltage ID is not valid. PM_FAIL When the average is not programmed.
pmErrCode_t PMHALINA226SetBusVoltConversionTime ( pmhalPrcmPmicRegulatorId_t  voltDomId,
pmhalIna226ConvTime_t  convTime 
)

Program the INA226 Bus Voltage measurement conversion time.

Parameters
voltDomIdVoltage Domain ID for which the value needs to be set. Refer pmhalPrcmPmicRegulatorId_t enum for valid values.
convTimeConversion Time for the given INA on the provided voltage rail. Refer pmhalIna226ConvTime_t for valid values.
Returns
status PM_SUCCESS When the conversion time is programmed. PM_BADARGS When the voltage ID is not valid. PM_FAIL When the conversion time is not programmed.

int32_t PMHALPrcmStatsGetCdRegData ( pmhalPrcmCdId_t  cdIdx,
pmhalCDStats_t *  cdStatus 
)

The API gets the Clock Domain Register details.

Parameters
cdIdxUnique Clock domain ID. Refer enum pmhalPrcmCdId_t for valid values.
cdStatusStructure to return the Clock domain status and list of Module elements in the Clock Domain.
Returns
status Status of the API. This can be the following values: PM_SUCCESS Indicates the operation is success PM_FAIL Indicates the API failed to complete the desired functionality. No valid Reg addr
